                        <div class="para-text">
                            Helpdesk is a portable desk and school bag, made out of recycled cardpaper and produced by women self groups in rural Maharashtra, India. It costs just INR10 to manufacture. <br><br>Kids in rural India walk miles to reach the
                            nearest school. The concept of carrying school bags, wearing shoes or a school uniform are distant dreams because most families are landless laborers who barely earn Rs.50 for 10 hours of work. Children often sit on the floor
                            to do their work without the aid of desks, and carry their books and materials home in flimsy, plastic shopping bags. Children who sit for long hours without the benefit of a desk can develop poor posture, eyesight problems
                            and even bad handwriting. Lack of school bags implies that students miss school in rainy season and many times it is the reason for their dropping off from school. <br><br>School bags and desks was an urgent problem to be fixed
                            for these kids, who easily number to 10 million.
                        </div>
                    </div>
